<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABT TO PREMIERE KUDELKA'S 'WORLD' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 American Ballet Theatre will dance the first West Coast performances of James 
Kudelka's "Cruel World" (set to Tchaikovsky's "Souvenir de Florence") on Sept. 
21 and 22 at the Orange County Performing Arts Center in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 Also on the mixed repertory program, the same each day, will be Twyla Tharp's 
"In the Upper Room" (music by Philip Glass) and Natalia Makarova's staging of 
"The Kingdom of the Shades" from "La Bayadere." 
</P>
<P>
 As previously announced, ABT will dance Kenneth MacMillan's "Manon" on Sept. 
20, 23, 24 and 25. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 556-2787. 
</P>
</TEXT>
