<P>
L.A. THEME SONG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One of the few mistakes made during the 1984 Olympics was the City Council's 
rejection of Randy Newman's "I Love L.A." as the official song for our 
city.This street-level, upbeat tribute made us feel good every time we heard 
it. 
</P>
<P>
 Since the collective opinions of our town have taken a nose-dive in the last 
10 years, embracing "I Love L.A." might be just the positive kick we need to 
start our spirits back up again. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles was a great place to live in 1984, and it's a great place to live 
today. Let's make "I Love L.A." official. 
</P>
<P>
 RON SALMONS 
</P>
