<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: QUAKE PREPARATION WORKSHOPS OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Earthquake-proofing workshops for homeowners and renters to prepare for the 
next big shaker will be offered this month at disaster assistance centers in 
Fillmore and Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The Federal Emergency Management Agency and the Governor's Office of Emergency 
Services will teach the workshops at the Fillmore center, 552 Sespe Ave., and 
the Simi Valley center, 59 Tierra Rejada Road. 
</P>
<P>
 One set of workshops will show renters how to make their belongings and their 
apartments or houses more resistant to earthquakes. The renters' workshops are 
scheduled for 10 a.m. Aug. 20 in Fillmore and 10 a.m. Aug. 27 in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Another workshop will teach homeowners how to strengthen their buildings 
against temblors by reinforcing walls, bolting foundations and strapping down 
chimneys. 
</P>
<P>
 It will be offered at 6:30 p.m. Aug. 23 in Fillmore. 
</P>
<P>
 A third set of workshops will teach homeowners and renters ways to fasten 
heavy furniture, overhead fixtures and water heaters inside their homes. 
</P>
<P>
 One workshop will be offered in English at 10 a.m. Aug. 27 in Fillmore. 
</P>
<P>
 The same workshop is offered in Spanish at 6:30 p.m. Tuesday in Fillmore and 
6:30 p.m. Aug. 23 in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 For information on these workshops and others in Los Angeles and Ventura 
counties, call the Disaster Helpline at (800) 525-0321. MACK REED 
</P>
</TEXT>
