<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROLLING CRIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Crime is on the rise. Our citizens are no longer safe in their 
neighborhoods.Recently one of our employees was going to the local bank to cash 
his first paycheck. He was abducted, beaten, slashed, robbed and dumped out 
left for dead alongside the freeway. It was hours before anyone found him. How 
do we protect ourselves from things like this? 
</P>
<P>
 We have to get involved in our community. Join or start a neighborhood watch 
program. We cannot let the criminals control our lives and take away our 
freedoms.  
</P>
<P>
 IRENE R. MAGALLANES 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 
</P>
