</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southern California College pitcher Ila Borders will have her jersey and the 
first ball she pitched in a college game inducted into the Orange County Hall 
of Fame. The ceremonies are Sept. 13 at Anaheim Stadium during the Orange 
County Sports Assn.'s "Newsmakers Luncheon." 
</P>
<P>
 Borders finished the season with a 2-4 record and a 2.91 earned-run average in 
49 1/3 innings. She walked 17 and struck out six in seven starts. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
