<HEADLINE>
<P>
EASY DAY FOR KLEIN TURNS SEMI-TOUGH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Emilee Klein of Studio City rolled into the semifinal round of match play 
Thursday with two victories in the Women's U.S. Amateur Championship at The 
Homestead's Cascade Course in Hot Springs, Va. 
</P>
<P>
 Klein romped to a 5 and 3 victory over Julie Brand of Ocala, Fla., in the 
morning round but had to rally for a 1-up, 19-hole victory in the afternoon 
against Denmark's Pernille Pedersen. 
</P>
<P>
 Pedersen had a two-hole lead with three to play and provided the start to 
Klein's rally by dumping her approach shot into the water on the 16th hole. 
</P>
<P>
 "She kind of gave me a gift," Klein said. 
</P>
<P>
 Klein, who played at Notre Dame High and is the NCAA Division I champion from 
Arizona State, will face Jill McGill of Denver in the semifinals today. Track 
and Field 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Wagenbach, the men's and women's cross-country coach at Mission College 
since 1980, will take over the men's track program at Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
 Wagenbach, who will continue to coach cross-country at Mission, will be 
assisted by Tim Knappen, a former Valley standout who won the pole vault in the 
1970 State junior college championships. Tennis 
</P>
<P>
 In a long-awaited showdown between the Valley's top two female juniors, 
top-seeded Meilen Tu of Northridge will meet No. 4 Ania Bleszynski of Thousand 
Oaks today. The two will play in the semifinals of the United States Tennis 
Assn. Girls' 18 National Championships in San Jose. 
</P>
<P>
 On Thursday, Tu defeated No. 5 Tara Snyder of Wichita, Kan., 6-1, 6-4. 
Bleszynski defeated No. 8 Jennifer Hall of Oklahoma City, 6-2, 4-6, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
 In other USTA national tournaments, No. 4 Mike Bryan of Camarillo defeated 
Nathan Overholser of Okemos, Mich., 6-2, 6-3, to advance to the quarterfinals 
of the rain-delayed boys' 16 tournament in Kalamazoo, Mich. 
</P>
<P>
 Erin Boisclair of Agoura Hills, ranked No. 1 in the nation, was upset in the 
quarterfinals of the girls' 16 tournament in San Diego. Her 7-6 (7-4), 6-1 loss 
to Tammy Encina of Miami Beach, Fla., however, was followed by a victory in 
doubles that will send Boisclair and Janet Walker of Seffner, Fla., to today's 
semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Bay Vo of Reseda beat Neil Hurlbut of Tucson, Ariz., 6-3, 7-5, to reach the 
semifinals of the men's 60 tournament in Santa Barbara. No. 8 John Bennett of 
West Hills fell to top-seeded King Van Nostrand of Bay Shore, N.Y., 6-3, 6-1. 
Baseball 
</P>
<P>
 The team representing the 818 and 805 area codes in next week's Area Code 
Games will play an exhibition doubleheader against the team from the 213 and 
310 area codes at 10 a.m. Sunday at Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 The Area Code Games begin Tuesday at Blair Field in Long Beach. Cycling 
</P>
<P>
 John Wordin of West Hills, a member of the Valley-based Nutra-Fig Racing Team, 
won the 10-mile Lake Piru Time Trial in 21 minutes eight seconds -- three 
seconds off the course record. Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge has hired Jeanette Armentano as an assistant to women's 
Coach Kim Chandler. 
