YOUTH BASEBALL; THOUSAND OAKS WINS WEST, ADVANCES TO WORLD SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shortstop Kevin Howard was three for four with two runs batted in, leading the 
Thousand Oaks Little League 13-year-old all-stars to a 7-4 victory against 
Pearl City, Hawaii, in the championship game of the West Regional on Thursday 
night in San Jose. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks will face Puerto Rico on Monday in the eight-team World Series 
in Taylor, Mich. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks broke a 2-2 tie with three runs in the bottom of the fourth 
inning, with the go-ahead run scoring on a single by Jeff Heyne. 
</P>
<P>
 Wes Munyon picked up the victory with two innings of relief. Munyon was also 
two for four with a double and a stolen base. Center fielder Fran Adams had a 
single and scored two runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Howard pitched the final three innings to pick up a save. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Westlake Senators' 14-year-olds beat Hawaii, 7-0, Thursday in the 
Continental Amateur Baseball Assn. World Series at Dublin, Ohio. The Senators 
played Kansas later Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Ralph Esparza pitched a two-hitter, striking out 11, to lead Westlake. Esparza 
also hit a home run and two singles. Eddie Loya and Ferman Bentancourt also 
doubled. 
</P>
<P>
 On Wednesday, Jeremy Sugarman pitched a four-hitter in Westlake's 6-2 victory 
over St. Louis. 
</P>
<P>
 The Senators also lost, 7-1, to Miami in nine innings on Wednesday night. Mike 
Falco took the loss after Miami scored six runs in the ninth inning. 
