<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE OUT: OC HIGH: STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS; CONDOM USE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuter 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Swiss teens head the safe sex league, a survey found. 
</P>
<P>
 The survey for British condom makers London International Group said 66 
percent of Swiss youngsters aged between 16 and 21 used a condom with a new 
partner. 
</P>
<P>
 The figure for their counterparts in Britain was 20 percent, in Italy 16 
percent, in France 12 percent and in Japan just 10 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
