<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE USUAL PAIR EXPECTED TO WIN THE ONE THAT GOT AWAY; VOLLEYBALL: KIRALY AND 
STEFFES, WHO HAVE WON 13 OF 19 TOURNAMENTS THIS YEAR, ARE FAVORITES IN SEAL 
BEACH OPEN THAT STARTS TODAY. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When the $100,000 Miller Lite Open beach volleyball tournament begins here 
today, there won't be any doubt which team is favored. 
</P>
<P>
 Karch Kiraly and Kent Steffes have won 13 of 19 tournaments this year and 50 
of their last 61. However, they have never teamed to win this event. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of 48 men's teams and eight women's teams will compete in the 
three-day event, which will feature the world's top professional beach 
volleyball players, including Randy Stoklos, Adam Johnson, Mike Dodd, Mike 
Whitmarsh, Tim Hovland, Nancy Reno, Angela Rock, Cammy Ciarelli and Holly 
McPeak. 
</P>
<P>
 Play will run from 9:30 a.m to 5 p.m. today, 8:30 a.m. to 1 p.m. Saturday and 
9 a.m. to about 1 p.m. Sunday, with the men's championship match scheduled for 
11:30 a.m. The women's final will be earlier, probably around 10. 
</P>
<P>
 The prize money for the men includes $20,000 for the first-place team; the 
women will play for $20,000, including $5,714 for the champions. 
</P>
<P>
 The matches will be played next to the Seal Beach Pier, at Eighth Street and 
Ocean Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 At last year's tournament, Kiraly and Steffes made it to the championship 
match but lost a grueling final to tour veterans Dodd and Whitmarsh. 
</P>
<P>
 On the women's side, Ciarelli and McPeak will be trying to defend their title. 
</P>
<P>
 Kiraly and Steffes, who played for UCLA, won 11 of the first 13 tournaments 
this season before Kiraly was sidelined for several weeks because of a bruised 
kidney suffered June 11 during a tour stop in Boulder, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
 The pair bounced back July 24 and won the championship match in Chicago and 
followed that with a victory last weekend in Santa Cruz. 
</P>
<P>
 Kiraly is third among active players in tournament victories with 92; Steffes 
is fourth with 67. Sinjin Smith, who will not participate because of lingering 
knee problems, leads all active players with 135 victories. Stoklos, the former 
longtime partner of Smith, has won 120 tournaments. 
</P>
<P>
 For the fourth consecutive year, the Miller Brewing Company will award 
$750,000 in bonus pool money for season-long point leaders on the AVP tour. 
</P>
<P>
 The bonuses, which will be awarded during the Hermosa Beach tournament in two 
weeks, include $100,000 for the point leader. The remainder will be shared 
among the rest of the top 48 players. 
</P>
<P>
 Each player receives 10.5 points for first place. Steffes currently holds a 
6.25-point advantage over Kiraly because Steffes earned points when he teamed 
with Scott Ayakatubby in Puerto Rico while Kiraly was sidelined with the kidney 
injury. 
</P>
<P>
 Dodd and Whitmarsh are third in the standings and trail Kiraly by 40 points. 
Past Seal Beach Winners 
</P>
<P>
 1993 -- Mike Dodd and Mike Whitmarsh (Cammy Ciarelli and Holly McPeak in 
women's division) 
</P>
<P>
