<P>
PHOTO ALBUM MAY REUNITE FAMILIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aid officials trying to find relatives for orphans and displaced Rwandan 
refugee children are hoping a huge photo album will help. 
</P>
<P>
 Eastman Kodak Co. agreed Thursday to donate 600 rolls of film and process 
photographs of up to 10,000 orphans or children separated from their parents 
during the flight from Rwanda, a U.N. aid official said. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.N. Children's Fund plans to compile the photos in a book that will be 
available to parents or relatives searching for their children. 
</P>
<P>
 "There are many children too young or too traumatized to give any 
information," said Christian Clark, a UNICEF spokesman. "Photos may be the only 
way to reunite people." 
