<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANADIAN WOMAN FINDS CONDOM IN WALNUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Canadian housewife opened a walnut and was shocked to find a condom inside. 
</P>
<P>
 "When I cracked one open for my son, I discovered a condom inside," Tracy 
Chalcraft of Chatham, Ontario, told the Canadian Press news agency. 
</P>
<P>
 The supermarket where she bought the nuts gave her a $20 food voucher as 
compensation, but its manager was at a loss for an explanation of how the 
unused prophylactic got there. 
</P>
<P>
 The item apparently came from a nearby sex shop that sells walnuts with 
condoms as a novelty, and a prankster may have tossed one into the 
supermarket's bulk foods section. 
</P>
</TEXT>
