METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SAN PEDRO; DETENTION 
CENTER NAMED AMONG TOP IN NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The San Pedro Service Processing Center has been named one of the nation's top 
detention facilities by the American Correctional Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 In becoming the third U.S. Immigration and Naturalization Service facility to 
receive the award, the San Pedro center received a perfect score in meeting the 
ACA's mandatory standards, and 99.13% in the non-mandatory standards, INS 
spokesman Rico Cabrera said. The study included a review of food service, 
training and lighting at the 450-bed facility.  
</P>
<P>
 The former home of the INS Western Regional Office underwent a $14-million 
renovation and was reopened as a detention center in 1991, Cabrera said. 
</P>
