<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; SPIRIT OF IRVINE RUN TO AID MAKE-A-WISH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Children and adults can walk or run in the sixth annual Spirit of Irvine Run 
on Saturday to benefit the Make-A-Wish Foundation of Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration opens at 6 a.m. at the Irvine Medical Center on Sand Canyon 
Avenue near Alton Parkway. 
</P>
<P>
 The event begins with a 5-kilometer run at 7:30 a.m., which will followed by a 
10-kilometer run at 8 a.m. The Kids' Fun Run begins at 9 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Entry fees are $12 ($18 with a T-shirt) for adults and $8 for children. All 
children who walk or run will get a T-shirt. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers will provide participants with refreshments, and awards will go to 
winners of the 5-kilometer and the 10-kilometer races. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is sponsored in conjunction with the Spirit of Irvine Festival on 
Saturday and Sunday at Heritage Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The Make-A-Wish Foundation grants wishes to terminally ill children. It hopes 
to raise $10,000 from the event, said Marlene Eckert, a foundation 
spokeswoman.LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</TEXT>
