KILLER-GANG MEMBER GETS 37 YEARS TO LIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANN W. O'NEILL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Juan (Slash) Garcia is headed to state prison for 37 years to life for the 
January, 1992, execution-style slaying of a rival gang member in the parking 
lot of the Odyssey restaurant, a prosecutor said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 San Fernando Superior Court Judge Meredith Taylor sentenced Garcia, 22, to the 
maximum sentence Thursday.Last month, a jury convicted Garcia of first-degree 
murder for shooting 17-year-old Martin Loziano, Deputy Dist. Atty. John 
Nantroup said.  
</P>
<P>
 The prosecutor said Loziano and two companions were enjoying the view from the 
hilltop parking lot of the Granada Hills restaurant in the 15600 block of 
Odyssey Drive when Garcia and two other suspected gang members drove up. An 
argument broke out, which led to the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 Nantroup said testimony showed that Loziano, already wounded, was hiding 
behind a palm tree when Garcia found him and fired the fatal shot into his 
head. 
</P>
<P>
 Two others were also injured. Tonya Marie Pineda, 18, was grazed by a bullet, 
and her brother-in-law, Daniel Pineda, 20, was shot through the thigh. Garcia 
also was convicted of assaulting Daniel Pineda with a firearm. 
</P>
