<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAN AFRICAN FILM FEST SETS OUTREACH PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The third annual Pan African Film Festival, to be held at Laemmle Sunset 5 
Theatres Oct. 12-26, is inviting L.A. County middle- and high-school teachers 
to have their students participate in StudentFest, a cinematic educational 
outreach program. 
</P>
<P>
 Students will be bused to the theater for a free screening of "More Time," a 
film from Zimbabwe focusing on the universal problems of youth in this time of 
AIDS, and discussions with filmmakers and community leaders. 
</P>
<P>
 Interested teachers and administrators may call the film festival office at 
(213) 295-1706. 
</P>
</TEXT>
