<TEXT>
<P>
 Money Supply Gauges Mixed: The Federal Reserve Board said that in the week 
ended Aug. 1, M2 rose to a seasonally adjusted $3,601.3 billion, up $600 
million from a revised $3,600.7 billion the week before.An even broader 
measure, M3, fell $4.9 billion to $4,239.2 billion from a revised $4,244.1 
billion. The narrowest measure, M1, rose $1 billion to $1,159.2 billion from 
$1,158.2 billion. M1 includes cash in circulation, deposits in checking 
accounts and non-bank traveler's checks. M2 is M1 plus accounts such as savings 
deposits and money market mutual funds. M3 is M2 plus less-liquid accounts, 
such as certificates of deposit in minimum denominations of $100,000. 
</P>
