<P>
 Avery Dennison Unit Plans Expansion: Materials Group North America said it 
will invest more than $150 million in boosting production of its Fasson brand 
paper and film label materials over the next three years. The Concord, 
Ohio-based unit of Avery Dennison Corp. also said its $30-million 
emulsion-adhesive coating plant, under construction in Greenfield, Ind., will 
begin operating in November, three months ahead of schedule, and that the new 
plant's capacity will be doubled in 1996. Materials Group is a major supplier 
of pressure-sensitive paper and film products. 
