<TEXT>
<P>
 Hostile Bid Rejected: Toronto-based Lac Minerals said it turned down a 
sweetened $1.74-billion bid from Royal Oak Mines Inc. Vancouver, Canada-based 
Royal Oak had raised its bid to $3.60 in cash plus two of its shares for each 
Lac share, valuing the offer at $12 a share -- a 45% premium to Lac's market 
price before Royal Oak's first bid was made July 7. Lac said it was concerned 
about the value of the stock being offered, the dilution to be suffered by 
stockholders because of the large amount of shares in the bid and the 
debt-heavy balance sheet of a combined company. 
</P>
