<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEALS: COMPANY TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN LIPPMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Films: Sony Pictures consolidated the motion picture marketing operations of 
Columbia Pictures and TriStar Pictures on Thursday under Columbia Pictures Vice 
Chairman Sid Ganis, the new president of worldwide marketing. In addition, 
Jeffrey Blake, president of domestic distribution for Columbia Pictures, was 
given the additional responsibility of overseeing the distribution operations 
of Triumph Releasing, which handles low-budget films.As part of the 
reorganization, Blake will also oversee distribution at Columbia and TriStar, 
although management said the two companies will continue to operate as 
stand-alone labels. Ganis will report to Columbia TriStar Chairman Mark Canton 
and President Fred Bernstein. Duncan Clark has been named executive vice 
president of worldwide marketing and will report to Ganis and J. Edward 
Shugrue, president of Columbia TriStar Film Distributors International. As a 
result of the shuffle, TriStar marketing presidents Buffy Shutt and Kathy 
Jones, who are being courted by rival studios, are leaving. And Canton, who 
joined Columbia three years ago, has signed a new three-year deal with Sony. 
JOHN LIPPMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
