<TEXT>
<P>
 Gish Biomedical Inc., an Irvine manufacturer of medical products, posted a 
profit of $1.3 million, or 41 cents a share, for the fiscal year ended June 30, 
down 28% from the $1.8 million, or 54 cents a share, recorded for the previous 
year.The company attributed the decline to higher research and development 
costs and to increased direct sales activity. Revenue remained at $21.1 
million. Fourth-quarter profit was down 4% from the like period a year ago, to 
$435,000, or 14 cents a share, from $452,000, or 14 cents a share. Sales dipped 
to $5.5 million from $5.7 million for fiscal 1993. 
